Issue with this:

    componentDidUpdate() {
        this.loadHeroes();
    }

is that `loadHeroes()` will change `state` and that will call `componentDidUpdate` again. Which will load heroes and change `state` :). Forever.

You probably want to re-`loadHeroes()` only and only if there are changes in `state.query`. To do that use `componentDidUpdate`&#39;s parameter `prevState`:

    componentDidUpdate(prevProps, prevState) {
        if (prevState.query != this.state.query) {
            this.loadHeroes();
        }
    }


[https://reactjs.org/docs/react-component.html#componentdidupdate][1]


  [1]: https://reactjs.org/docs/react-component.html#componentdidupdate

